@lacoste x @godzillas_us returns with a roar⁠
⁠
The second collaboration drops May 29, 2026, with early access from April 25 at the new Shinjuku store. Featuring a navy-led palette, the collection expands the “Godzilla + Lacoste” logo with new designs like Mechagodzilla and “Team Godzilla,” plus apparel and accessories ranging from tees and polos to bags and caps. Shinjuku-exclusive items and in-store installations add extra heat, with a follow-up pop-up in Kyoto in June.

@ys_theofficial everyday line, has created a bespoke jacket for the hosts of @aesop Factory of Light at Milan’s Salone del Mobile. Designed with a relaxed, functional silhouette, the piece features a large waist patch pocket and inner chest pocket, finished in a softly wrinkled texture achieved through a vintage processing technique. The result is a quietly expressive uniform that mirrors the role of its wearers: guiding, assisting, and welcoming guests through the immersive installation.⁠
⁠
The collaboration brings together two like-minded nonconformists. Y’s and Aesop share a restrained aesthetic, a love for asymmetry, and a poetic approach to daily rituals. Now in its third year at Salone, Aesop’s Factory of Light explores craft, illumination, and human touch through a multi-sensory experience — echoing the brand’s ability to subtly transform both spaces and skin.

@newbalance x @doverstreetmarketnewyork 🏃has arrived with a sleek and discreet running-focused collection. The collaboration is led by an exclusive New Balance SC Elite V5, a lightweight model that features a carbon fiber plate and an “ultra-responsive “PEBA midsole. Joining the deep purple-hued SC Elite V5 is a range of athletic apparel, including the Race Day Ultra Light T-shirt, a panelled windbreaker, and high-cut split shorts. ⁠
Shop the collection now exclusively at Dover Street Market.
Photo: Dover Street Market/Kingsley Ifill

@JacobAndCo. unveils the Godfather II, a $440,000 musical timepiece that brings cinema to the wrist.
Drawing inspiration from one of film’s most iconic sagas, the watch integrates two legendary compositions — The Godfather’s Waltz and The Godfather Love Theme — played through an intricate, built-in music box.
Encased in a sculpted Art Deco-inspired design, the piece combines horological artistry with cinematic storytelling. A flying tourbillon, dual power reserves, and a newly engineered movement elevate both its technical and aesthetic appeal, while the dial features a finely detailed portrait of Don Corleone alongside subtle references to the film’s legacy.
Limited to just 74 pieces, in tribute to the 1974 release of The Godfather Part II, the timepiece stands as a rare collector’s creation, where music, craftsmanship, and heritage converge.
